projects.name: Random-Password-Generator
projects.description: Developed a Python project using Graphical User Interface (GUI) techniques to create a Random Password Generator. This program harnesses the power of a pseudo-random number generator. This Gui application automatically generate secure and unique passwords, enhancing data security and user convenience.

projects.name: ERP-Portal
projects.description: In the ERP Portal project, HTML and Python are used to build the user interface and backend functionalities, respectively. Frameworks like Django are commonly used in such projects for handling server-side operations, database integration, and dynamic content rendering. This combination provides a full-stack solution to manage essential college operations such as student information, course management, and administrative tasks.

projects.name: Quiz-maker

experiences.description: Completed an internship at APSSDC, where I refined my data analysis skills using Python. The Project Screen Time Analysis takes the data of the apps being used in our mobiles and show us the record of it and its usage using Data Visualization. The key points are data cleaning, preprocessing techniques, and visualization. This experience provided valuable insights into data-driven decision-making, enhancing my readiness for professional roles.
